findings, since it already discusses how theoretical predictions align with empirical results. I'll add the 32K results there as a qualification showing where the theory diverges from practice in longer contexts. I need to strategically add the long-context results without disrupting the flow—inserting a new subsection after the E75/E87 table with the 32K evaluation data, updating the theory-versus-practice comparison table to include this case, and revising the conclusion to reflect that the empirical results now align with theoretical predictions at longer contexts. Generating the results table...\n\nThe gap between E88 and Mamba2 flips dramatically at longer context—E88 trails by 0.04 nats at 512 tokens but pulls ahead by 0.088 nats at 32K, suggesting its nonlinear-in-time design really shines with extended sequences. E88 achieves this by scaling its memory heads rather than depth, and across the board these models favor wider state representations when handling longer contexts. Now I'm updating the theory-versus-practice comparison to capture where each architecture actually dominates.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8657,"cache_read_input_tokens":31645,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8657},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e61ab93-090b-4bfe-8c5a-2de594a57979","uuid":"2c2dbf3c-33b5-4c31-a2dd-e79fbabc652d"}
